Call for Papers: Conferences in Toronto and Paris
Posted on 2012/04/02. Filed under: 管理, 經濟, 綜合, 財務, 會計 | 標籤：2012.05 報名截止, 2012.06 報名截止, Business, Marketing |  
Dear Colleague
Please see below regarding details of Call For Papers for two upcoming conferences in Toronto, Canada and Paris, France.
Call For Papers
17th International Business Research Conference
DATES: 7-8 June 2012
VENUE: Ryerson University, Toronto, Canada
Submission Deadline: 11 May 2012 and Registration Deadline: 25 May 2012
Website: www.conferencebulletin.org
Full-length papers, research-in-progress papers, case studies and /or abstracts, relating to all areas of Accounting, Banking , Business Law, Finance, Economics, Investment, Management, Marketing, E-Commerce and all other areas of Business Studies are invited for the above international conference. An author can present up to two papers. This conference is sponsored by eight international peer reviewed journals, WBI London, World Business Institute, Australia, and Business Care Aust P/L, USA 
· Submission, Review Process and Announcement of Acceptance:
Please email to papsconfo(at)gmail.com by 11 May 2012 a copy of a completed paper and/or an abstract which will be reviewed anonymously. Review process will determine the quality and suitability of the paper for the conference. Author will be notified review outcome within two weeks after arrival of the paper. The cover page should include the affiliation, address, phone and email of each author and subject track and/or the appropriate JEL classifications. 
 • Written Feedback and Publications Opportunity 
You will receive written feedback on your paper after the conference. Quality papers will be considered for publication in the following international peer reviewed and Cabell indexed journals with ISSN : Journal of Business and Policy Research. World Journal of Management, Global Economy and Finance Journal, International Review of Business Research Papers, Global Review of Accounting and Finance and World Review of Business Research subject to compliance to review report, editorial comments, conference feedback and payment of applicable subscription fees.
• Awards and Conference Proceedings and other Benefits
Best paper award will be announced from a block of 10 papers in each track and will be published in any of the above journals and a certificate will be issued at the conference dinner. All accepted abstract and full papers will be published in the refereed conference proceedings with ISBN and will be published electronically via a separate website, namely, www.wbiconpro.com. There is an option that the participant can serve as session chair and/or discussant of a paper of his/her own area of interest and certificate will be issued to such participant. 
How To Submit Papers
Send your paper to: Dr. Mohammad Hoque via email address: papsconfo(at)gmail.com 
Program Chairs:
Professor Peter Yannopoulos, Brock University, Canada
Professor William Lim, York University, Canada
Call for Papers
Annual Paris Conference on “Business and Social Sciences”
Date: 12-13 July 2012 | Venue: Hotel Novotel Paris Tour de Eiffel, France
Submission deadline: 4 June 2012 | Registration Deadline: 29 June 2012
Website: www.infoconfo.com Email to: parisconpap(at)gmail.com
Research papers in all areas of Accounting, Banking, Economics, Finance, Investment, Management, Marketing and Business Education are invited for the above international conference organised by European Centre for Business and Economic Research (ECBER), WBI London BCA Aust ( USA), and World Business Institute, Australia and sponsored by six international peer reviewed refereed journals: Global Economics and Finance Journals, International Review of Business Research Papers, Journal of Business and Policy Research, World Journal of Management, Global Review of Accounting and Finance and World Review Business Research which are indexed by Cabell’s Directory of USA
PAPER SUBMISSION GUIDELINES, REVIEW PROCESS & ACCEPTANCE NOTICE:
Please email by the deadline a copy of a Completed or Nearly Completed Paper or an Abstract in word file. The cover page should include the author(s) name, affiliation, address, phone and email of each author and the name of the track such as “finance”. All papers will be blind reviewed and outcome in terms of whether accepted or not will be announced within two weeks after arrival of the paper.
PROCEEDINDS, BEST PAPER AWARD & PUBLICATION OPPORTUNITIES:
In addition to online refereed conference proceedings with ISBN, outstanding papers will be considered for publication in one of the ABOVE sponsoring journals. You can serve as a chair of the session, designated discussant or reviewer which will be rewarded by a certificate and 5% discount on registration fees. Best paper award will be announced from a block of each 10 papers and will be published in our journals without any cost.
REGISTRATION FEES AND PUBLICATION FEES: 
Basic registration fee (includes 2 lunch and break-foods for 2 days) plus conference proceedings : US$550
Student Delegate Fee : 10% discount
If your paper is accepted by a particular journal, you need to pay publication fee US$300 per paper for both print & online version or US$150 for online version only.
WHO TO SEND PAPERS : Please send your paper to Dr. Mohammad Hoque, Chair-Paper Review Committee via parisconpap(at)gmail.com
FURTHER INFORMATION : Further information regarding the conference fees, accommodations, visa and publication opportunity, please visit the conference website.
PROGRAM CHAIR
Professor Marc Pilkington, Université de Nice Sophia Antipolis, France
